{
  "type": "spell",
  "name": "Bony Barrage",
  "folder": null,
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You shatter the skeleton of a thrall within 30 feet, destroying it and creating a volley of phalanges, teeth, and vertebrae in a 30-foot cone from where the thrall was. Each creature in the area takes 2d10 piercing damage with a basic Reflex save. When you cast bony barrage, you can shatter a second thrall in the cone's area to cover your allies in bone armor. If you do, the cone doesn't affect your allies, and any ally in the area gains a +1 status bonus to AC until the start of your next turn. Each thrall you shatter is destroyed.</p><hr /><p><strong>Heightened (+1)</strong> The damage increases by 1d10.</p>"
